casebody.data:
The VON HAMM YOUNG COMPANY, Limited, Claimant of One Packard Convertible Coupe, etc., v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 9121. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 13, 1939. Thompson & Russell, of Honolulu, T. H., for appellant. I. M. Stainback, U. S. Atty., and J. Frank McLaughlin, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Honolulu, T. H.

Before GARRECHT, HANEY, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
